  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Part-Time Customer Experience Officer",
  "description": "<p>As a Customer Experience Officer (CX), you will be the first point of contact for our customers and play a key role in ensuring a smooth, warm, and professional experience across our outlets and communication channels. This role requires strong attention to detail, reliability, and genuine care for both customers and cats.</p><p>You will work closely with the operations and grooming/boarding teams to manage customer enquiries, bookings, and on-ground support, especially during peak periods.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Handle customer enquiries via WhatsApp, phone calls, and in-person interactions</p></li><li><p>Manage bookings, schedules, and customer requests accurately</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with caretakers, groomers and outlet teams to ensure smooth daily operations</p></li><li><p>Handle customer feedback, concerns, and follow-ups professionally</p></li><li><p>Ensure accurate documentation and updates in internal systems</p></li><li><p>Support outlet operations during busy periods when required</p></li><li><p>Uphold service standards and company policies at all times</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><p><strong>Availability & Commitment</strong></p><ul><li><p>Able to commit to <strong>a minimum of 4 days per week</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Weekend availability is mandatory</strong></p></li><li><p>Able to commit to a consistent, long-term part-time schedule</p></li></ul><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prior experience in:</p><ul><li><p>Customer service, OR</p></li><li><p>Animal care / pet-related industry (e.g. cat care, boarding, grooming, veterinary support)</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Experience working in fast-paced or customer-facing environments is preferred</p></li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></p><ul><li><p>Good written and spoken English</p></li><li><p>Comfortable communicating with customers professionally and empathetically</p></li><li><p>Able to follow SOPs, policies, and structured workflows</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented and organised</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working with digital systems (e.g. booking platforms, internal tools)</p></li></ul><p><strong>Personal Attributes</strong></p><ul><li><p>Genuine care and respect for animals, especially cats</p></li><li><p>Responsible, reliable, and able to work independently</p></li><li><p>Calm and composed when handling customer issues</p></li><li><p>Team-oriented with a positive work attitude</p></li></ul>",
